text: The Constitutional Court () is the supreme interpreter of the Spanish Constitution. 8/1984, 4/1985, 6/1988, 7/1999 and 1/2000. The court is the "supreme interpreter" of the Constitution, but since the court is not a part of the Spanish Judiciary, the Supreme Court is the highest court for all judicial matters.ยง 123, clause 1, Spanish Constitution of 1978. ==References== Category:Law of Spain Category:National supreme courts
title: Constitutional Court of Spain
